## How to use it with AI agents (MCP), Claude, and the API

### Claude Desktop / Claude Code via Apify MCP
```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "apify": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "@apify/actors-mcp-server", "--actors", "__USERNAME__/__SLUG__"],
      "env": { "APIFY_TOKEN": "<YOUR_APIFY_TOKEN>" }
    }
  }
}
```

### Python (Apify API)
```python
from apify_client import ApifyClient
client = ApifyClient("<YOUR_APIFY_TOKEN>")
run = client.actor("__USERNAME__/__SLUG__").call(run_input=__SAMPLE_INPUT_PY__)
for item in client.dataset(run["defaultDatasetId"]).iterate_items():
    print(item)
```

### TypeScript (Apify API)
```ts
import { ApifyClient } from 'apify-client';
const client = new ApifyClient({ token: '<YOUR_APIFY_TOKEN>' });
const run = await client.actor('__USERNAME__/__SLUG__').call(__SAMPLE_INPUT__);
const { items } = await client.dataset(run.defaultDatasetId).listItems();
console.log(items);
```

### LangChain / CrewAI tool
```python
from langchain_apify import ApifyActorsTool
tool = ApifyActorsTool("__USERNAME__/__SLUG__")  # agent calls it autonomously
```

